<DOC><DOCNO> AP880829-0024 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-29-88 0028EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u a AM-GrenadeExplodes     08-29 0249</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Grenade Explodes,0255</SECOND><HEAD>7 Hurt As Grenade Explodes In Racial Confrontation</HEAD><DATELINE>BRADENTON, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A racial confrontation between whiteswielding baseball bats and rock- and bottle-throwing blacksculminated Sunday in the explosion of a grenade, which injuredseven people, authorities said.   Four of the injured were juveniles, including a 12-year-old.None of the injuries appeared critical, but one 17-year-old boy wasadmitted to Manatee Memorial Hospital for treatment, authoritiessaid.   The Manatee County sheriff's office, still trying to piecetogether information late Sunday, could not confirm a report thatthere was shooting with an automatic weapon.   Manatee County Sheriff Charlie Wells said authorities believethey know who threw the grenade, but no arrests had been made bylate Sunday after the incident in the parking lot of a conveniencestore.   The sheriff's office said all of the injured were black, exceptfor one 28-year-old man.   The incident broke out about 6:45 p.m. between a group of blacksstanding in the parking lot and a group of whites who had gatheredat an adjacent bar, Wells said.   ``It does not appear to be a strictly racial incident eventhough the situation basically is between whites and blacks,''Wells told The Bradenton Herald. ``It does not appear to beanything that's brewing over a period of time from what we can findout.''   However, several residents told the newspaper that racialtensions have run high in the racially mixed neighborhood calledDuplex City since the opening of the bar.</TEXT></DOC>